The Constitution Phase establishes the foundation of the entire project. It defines the projectâ€™s purpose, mission, scope, goals, values, constraints, and success criteria. This phase ensures everyone understands why the project exists before development begins.

2ï¸âƒ£ Specify Phase

The Specify Phase transforms the project vision into detailed, clear, and testable requirements. This includes defining user stories, acceptance criteria, stakeholders, and system behaviors. It ensures developers and AI agents know exactly what needs to be built.

3ï¸âƒ£ Plan Phase

The Plan Phase outlines the execution strategy. It includes milestones, workflows, timelines, risks, and dependency mapping. This step turns requirements into a structured development roadmap, ensuring smooth and predictable progress.

4ï¸âƒ£ Tasks Phase

In the Tasks Phase, the work is broken into small, independent, and actionable tasks. Each task includes instructions, expected outputs, tools, and assigned responsibilities. This allows for efficient parallel development and reduces bottlenecks.

5ï¸âƒ£ Implement Phase

The Implement Phase is where actual development happens. Developers and AI agents build features, test components, integrate systems, and deliver working outputs based on the tasks defined earlier. This phase focuses on quality delivery and continuous improvement.

